#X text 22 960 The "pop" method will remove the last element in the
array and return its value. The interesting thing about this in PD
is that we need to know the length of the array before we start (hence
another situation where [arraysize] is an essential tool). "Pushing"
is the opposite effect and also a tool provided in Java. When an array
is pushed \, an element is added to the array and the new size is returned.
;
