#X text 582 104 expression evaluation family - expr \, expr~ \, fexpr~
;
#X text 481 356 Syntyax:;
#X text 580 405 $f#: float input variable;
#X text 581 420 $s#: symbol input variable;
#X text 579 245 expr~ is used for expression evaluaion of signal data
on the vector by vector basis;
#X text 579 230 expr is used for expression evaluaion of control data
;
#X text 583 133 For a more detailed documentaion refer to http://www.crca.ucsd.edu/~yadegari/expr.html
;
#X text 580 348 The syntax is very close to how expressions are written
in C. Variables are specified as follows where the '#' stands for the
inlet number:;
#X text 581 391 $i#: integer input variable;
#X text 579 273 fexpr~ is used for expression evaluaion on sample level
data \; i.e. \, filter design. Warning: fexpr~ is very cpu intensive.
;
#X text 583 179 you can define multiple expressoins in the same object.
semicolon is used to separates the expressions.;
